{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":873,"text":"A couple of years ago,"},{"time":2055,"text":"when I was attending\nthe TED conference in Long Beach,"},{"time":5188,"text":"I met Harriet."},{"time":6577,"text":"We'd actually met online before --\nnot the way you're thinking."},{"time":10000,"text":"We were introduced\nbecause we both knew Linda Avey,"},{"time":12459,"text":"one of the founders of the first\nonline personal genomic companies."},{"time":15787,"text":"And because we shared\nour genetic information with Linda,"},{"time":18508,"text":"she could see that Harriet and I shared"},{"time":20439,"text":"a very rare type of mitochondrial DNA,\nhaplotype K1a1b1a,"},{"time":24353,"text":"which meant we were distantly related."},{"time":26372,"text":"We actually share the same\ngenealogy with Ötzi the Iceman."},{"time":29229,"text":"So -- Ötzi, Harriet and me."},{"time":30764,"text":"And being the current day, of course,\nwe started our own Facebook group."},{"time":34189,"text":"You're all welcome to join."},{"time":35512,"text":"When I met Harriet in person\nthe next year at the TED conference,"},{"time":38616,"text":"she'd gone online and ordered\nour own happy haplotype T-shirts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41628,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":42663,"text":"Why am I telling you this story?"},{"time":44230,"text":"What does it have to do\nwith the future of health?"},{"time":46596,"text":"Well, the way I met Harriet is an example"},{"time":48596,"text":"of how leveraging cross-disciplinary,\nexponentially growing technologies"},{"time":52371,"text":"is affecting our future\nof health and wellness --"},{"time":54706,"text":"from low-cost gene analysis"},{"time":56080,"text":"to the ability to do\npowerful bioinformatics"},{"time":58222,"text":"to the connection of the Internet\nand social networking."},{"time":61589,"text":"What I'd like to talk about today"},{"time":63213,"text":"is understanding\nthese exponential technologies."},{"time":65497,"text":"We often think linearly."},{"time":67078,"text":"But if you think about it,\nif you have a lily pad"},{"time":69690,"text":"and it just divided every single day --"},{"time":71677,"text":"two, four, eight, sixteen --\nin 15 days, you'd have 32,000."},{"time":75357,"text":"What do you think you'd have in a month?"},{"time":77316,"text":"We're at a billion."},{"time":78491,"text":"If we start to think exponentially,"},{"time":80187,"text":"we can see how this is starting to affect\nall the technologies around us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83663,"text":"Many of these technologies,\nspeaking as a physician and innovator,"},{"time":86790,"text":"we can start to leverage,\nto impact the future of our own health"},{"time":89906,"text":"and of health care,"},{"time":91081,"text":"and to address many of the major\nchallenges in health care today,"},{"time":94190,"text":"ranging from the exponential costs\nto the aging population,"},{"time":97379,"text":"the way we really don't use\ninformation very well today,"},{"time":100103,"text":"the fragmentation of care"},{"time":101617,"text":"and the often very difficult course\nof adoption of innovation."},{"time":105371,"text":"And one of the major things we can do\nis move the curve to the left."},{"time":109190,"text":"We spend most of our money\non the last 20 percent of life."},{"time":111931,"text":"What if we could incentivize physicians\nin the health care system"},{"time":115015,"text":"and our own selves"},{"time":116195,"text":"to move the curve to the left\nand improve our health,"},{"time":118734,"text":"leveraging technology as well?"},{"time":120202,"text":"Now my favorite example\nof exponential technology,"},{"time":122650,"text":"we all have in our pocket."},{"time":123974,"text":"If you think about it,\nthese are really dramatically improving."},{"time":127269,"text":"I mean, this is the iPhone 4."},{"time":129199,"text":"Imagine what the iPhone 8\nwill be able to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132411,"text":"Now, I've gained some insight into this."},{"time":134353,"text":"I've been the track share\nfor the medicine portion"},{"time":136952,"text":"of a new institution\ncalled Singularity University,"},{"time":139483,"text":"based in Silicon Valley."},{"time":140896,"text":"We bring together each summer\nabout 100 very talented students"},{"time":143880,"text":"from around the world."},{"time":145070,"text":"And we look at these exponential\ntechnologies from medicine,"},{"time":147960,"text":"biotech, artificial intelligence,\nrobotics, nanotechnology, space,"},{"time":151130,"text":"and address how we can cross-train\nand leverage these"},{"time":153633,"text":"to impact major unmet goals."},{"time":154997,"text":"We also have seven-day executive programs."},{"time":157028,"text":"And coming up next month is FutureMed,"},{"time":159435,"text":"a program to help cross-train\nand leverage technologies into medicine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162833,"text":"Now, I mentioned the phone."},{"time":164378,"text":"These mobile phones have over 20,000\ndifferent mobile apps available."},{"time":167713,"text":"There's one out of the UK\nwhere you can pee on a little chip,"},{"time":170979,"text":"connect it to your iPhone,"},{"time":172284,"text":"and check for an STD."},{"time":173463,"text":"I don't know if I'd try that,\nbut it's available."},{"time":175790,"text":"There are other sorts of applications."},{"time":177639,"text":"Merging your phone\nand diagnostics, for example,"},{"time":179939,"text":"measuring your blood glucose\non your iPhone"},{"time":182004,"text":"and sending that to your physician,"},{"time":183735,"text":"so they can better understand\nand you can better understand"},{"time":186526,"text":"your blood sugars as a diabetic."},{"time":188130,"text":"So let's see how exponential\ntechnologies are taking health care."},{"time":191275,"text":"Let's start with faster."},{"time":192465,"text":"It's no secret that computers,\nthrough Moore's law,"},{"time":194898,"text":"are speeding up faster and faster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196565,"text":"We can do more powerful things with them."},{"time":198650,"text":"They're really approaching --\nin many cases, surpassing --"},{"time":201475,"text":"the ability of the human mind."},{"time":202945,"text":"But where I think computational speed\nis most applicable is in imaging."},{"time":206803,"text":"The ability now to look\ninside the body in real time"},{"time":209459,"text":"with very high resolution"},{"time":210941,"text":"is really becoming incredible."},{"time":212425,"text":"And we're layering multiple\ntechnologies -- PET scans, CT scans"},{"time":215485,"text":"and molecular diagnostics --"},{"time":217531,"text":"to find and seek things\nat different levels."},{"time":220356,"text":"Here you're going to see the very highest\nresolution MRI scan done today,"},{"time":223831,"text":"of Marc Hodosh, the curator of TEDMED."},{"time":226674,"text":"And now we can see inside of the brain"},{"time":228841,"text":"at a resolution and ability\nnever before available,"},{"time":231457,"text":"and essentially learn how to reconstruct\nand maybe even reengineer"},{"time":235547,"text":"or backwards engineer the brain,"},{"time":237255,"text":"so we can better understand\npathology, disease and therapy."},{"time":240256,"text":"We can look inside with real-time\nfMRI in the brain at real time."},{"time":243572,"text":"And by understanding these sorts\nof processes and these connections,"},{"time":246885,"text":"we're going to understand the effects\nof medication or meditation"},{"time":249972,"text":"and better personalize\nand make effective, for example,"},{"time":252603,"text":"psychoactive drugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254230,"text":"The scanners for these are getting\nsmaller, less expensive"},{"time":257022,"text":"and more portable."},{"time":258197,"text":"And this sort of data explosion\navailable from these"},{"time":260692,"text":"is really almost becoming a challenge."},{"time":262650,"text":"The scan of today takes up\nabout 800 books, or 20 gigabytes."},{"time":265651,"text":"The scan in a couple of years\nwill be one terabyte, or 800,000 books."},{"time":268946,"text":"How do you leverage that information?"},{"time":270739,"text":"Let's get personal."},{"time":271914,"text":"I won't ask who here's had a colonoscopy,\nbut if you're over age 50,"},{"time":275145,"text":"it's time for your screening colonoscopy."},{"time":277162,"text":"How'd you like to avoid\nthe pointy end of the stick?"},{"time":279617,"text":"Now there's essentially\nvirtual colonoscopy."},{"time":281692,"text":"Compare those two pictures."},{"time":283007,"text":"As a radiologist, you can basically\nfly through your patient's colon,"},{"time":286298,"text":"and augmenting that\nwith artificial intelligence,"},{"time":288617,"text":"potentially identify a lesion\nthat we might have missed,"},{"time":291270,"text":"but using AI on top of radiology,"},{"time":292870,"text":"we can find lesions\nthat were missed before."},{"time":294945,"text":"Maybe this will encourage\npeople to get colonoscopies"},{"time":297496,"text":"that wouldn't have otherwise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298903,"text":"This is an example of this paradigm shift."},{"time":300939,"text":"We're moving to this integration\nof biomedicine, information technology,"},{"time":304364,"text":"wireless and, I would say, mobile now --\nthis era of digital medicine."},{"time":307694,"text":"Even my stethoscope is now digital,\nand of course, there's an app for that."},{"time":311262,"text":"We're moving, obviously,\nto the era of the tricorder."},{"time":313821,"text":"So the handheld ultrasound\nis basically surpassing"},{"time":316294,"text":"and supplanting the stethoscope."},{"time":318316,"text":"These are now at a price point\nof what used to be 100,000 euros"},{"time":321302,"text":"or a couple hundred-thousand dollars."},{"time":323165,"text":"For about 5,000 dollars,"},{"time":324342,"text":"I can have the power of a very powerful\ndiagnostic device in my hand."},{"time":327692,"text":"Merging this now with the advent\nof electronic medical records --"},{"time":330808,"text":"in the US, we're still\nless than 20 percent electronic;"},{"time":333413,"text":"here in the Netherlands,\nI think it's more than 80 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336233,"text":"Now that we're switching\nto merging medical data,"},{"time":338545,"text":"making it available electronically,"},{"time":340244,"text":"we can crowd-source the information,\nand as a physician,"},{"time":342916,"text":"I can access my patients' data\nfrom wherever I am,"},{"time":345276,"text":"just through my mobile device."},{"time":346730,"text":"And now, of course, we're in the era\nof the iPad, even the iPad 2."},{"time":349867,"text":"Just last month,"},{"time":351042,"text":"the first FDA-approved\napplication was approved"},{"time":353281,"text":"to allow radiologists to do actual\nreading on these sorts of devices."},{"time":356798,"text":"So certainly, the physicians\nof today, including myself,"},{"time":359443,"text":"are completely reliable on these devices."},{"time":361444,"text":"And as you saw just about a month ago,"},{"time":363287,"text":"Watson from IBM beat\nthe two champions in \"Jeopardy.\""},{"time":365804,"text":"So I want you to imagine\nwhen, in a couple of years,"},{"time":368266,"text":"we've started to apply\nthis cloud-based information,"},{"time":370750,"text":"when we really have the AI physician\nand leverage our brains to connectivity"},{"time":374374,"text":"to make decisions and diagnostics\nat a level never done."},{"time":377348,"text":"Already today, you don't need to go\nto your physician in many cases."},{"time":380571,"text":"Only in about 20 percent of visits\ndo you need to lay hands on the patient."},{"time":384137,"text":"We're now in the era of virtual visits."},{"time":386022,"text":"From Skype-type visits\nyou can do with American Well,"},{"time":388539,"text":"to Cisco, that's developed a very complex\nhealth presence system,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":391620,"text":"the ability to interact with\nyour health care provider is different."},{"time":394851,"text":"And these are being augmented\neven by our devices, again, today."},{"time":397900,"text":"My friend Jessica sent me\na picture of her head laceration,"},{"time":400693,"text":"so I can save her a trip\nto the emergency room,"},{"time":402925,"text":"and do diagnostics that way."},{"time":404378,"text":"Or maybe we can leverage\ntoday's gaming technology,"},{"time":406796,"text":"like the Microsoft Kinect,"},{"time":408066,"text":"hack that to enable diagnostics,\nfor example, in diagnosing stroke,"},{"time":411267,"text":"using simple motion detection,\nusing $100 devices."},{"time":413880,"text":"We can actually now visit\nour patients robotically."},{"time":417089,"text":"This is the RP7;"},{"time":418264,"text":"if I'm a hematologist,\nI can visit another clinic or hospital."},{"time":421246,"text":"These are being augmented\nby a whole suite of tools"},{"time":423665,"text":"actually in the home now."},{"time":424885,"text":"We already have wireless scales."},{"time":426763,"text":"You step on the scale,\ntweet your weight to your friends,"},{"time":429492,"text":"they can keep you in line."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430758,"text":"We have wireless blood pressure cuffs."},{"time":432600,"text":"A whole gamut of technologies\nare being put together."},{"time":435131,"text":"Instead of wearing kludgy devices,\nwe put on a simple patch."},{"time":437969,"text":"This was developed at Stanford."},{"time":439486,"text":"It's called iRhythm; it completely\nsupplants the prior technology"},{"time":442589,"text":"at a much lower price point,\nwith much more effectivity."},{"time":445265,"text":"We're also in the era today\nof quantified self."},{"time":447764,"text":"Consumers now can basically buy\n$100 devices, like this little Fitbit."},{"time":451393,"text":"I can measure my steps,\nmy caloric outtake."},{"time":453438,"text":"I can get insight into that\non a daily basis"},{"time":455515,"text":"and share it with my friends or physician."},{"time":457547,"text":"There's watches that measure\nyour heart rate, Zeo sleep monitors,"},{"time":460650,"text":"a suite of tools\nthat enable you to leverage"},{"time":462757,"text":"and have insight into your own health."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464595,"text":"As we start to integrate this information,"},{"time":466627,"text":"we'll know better what to do with it,\nand have better insight"},{"time":469532,"text":"into our own pathologies,\nhealth and wellness."},{"time":471983,"text":"There's even mirrors\nthat can pick up your pulse rate."},{"time":474650,"text":"And I would argue, in the future,"},{"time":476433,"text":"we'll have wearable devices\nin our clothes, monitoring us 24/7."},{"time":479619,"text":"And just like the OnStar system\nin cars, your red light might go on."},{"time":483060,"text":"It won't say \"check engine\";\nit'll be a \"check your body\" light,"},{"time":486129,"text":"and you'll go get it taken care of."},{"time":487837,"text":"Probably in a few years,"},{"time":489034,"text":"you'll look in your mirror\nand it'll be diagnosing you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491864,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":493110,"text":"For those of you with kiddos at home,"},{"time":495213,"text":"how would you like a wireless\ndiaper that supports your --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":498182,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":499266,"text":"More information, I think,\nthan you might need,"},{"time":501487,"text":"but it's going to be here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502948,"text":"Now, we've heard a lot today\nabout technology and connection."},{"time":506072,"text":"And I think some of these technologies"},{"time":507908,"text":"will enable us to be more connected\nwith our patients, to take more time"},{"time":511350,"text":"and do the important\nhuman-touch elements of medicine,"},{"time":513955,"text":"as augmented by these technologies."},{"time":515657,"text":"Now, we've talked about\naugmenting the patient."},{"time":518050,"text":"How about augmenting the physician?"},{"time":519750,"text":"We're now in the era\nof super-enabling the surgeon,"},{"time":522164,"text":"who can now go into the body and do\nrobotic surgery, which is here today,"},{"time":525650,"text":"at a level that was not really possible\neven five years ago."},{"time":529137,"text":"And now this is being augmented\nwith further layers of technology,"},{"time":532281,"text":"like augmented reality."},{"time":533460,"text":"So the surgeon can see\ninside the patient, through their lens,"},{"time":536415,"text":"where the tumor is,\nwhere the blood vessels are."},{"time":538750,"text":"This can be integrated\nwith decision support."},{"time":540879,"text":"A surgeon in New York can help\na surgeon in Amsterdam, for example."},{"time":544064,"text":"And we're entering an era\nof truly scarless surgery called NOTES,"},{"time":547464,"text":"where the robotic endoscope\ncan come out the stomach"},{"time":550079,"text":"and pull out that gallbladder,"},{"time":551551,"text":"all in a scarless way and robotically."},{"time":553926,"text":"This is called NOTES, and it's coming --\nbasically scarless surgery,"},{"time":557266,"text":"as mediated by robotic surgery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559348,"text":"Now, how about controlling other elements?"},{"time":561468,"text":"For those who have\ndisabilities -- the paraplegic,"},{"time":563922,"text":"there's the brain-computer\ninterface, or BCI,"},{"time":566733,"text":"where chips have been put\non the motor cortex"},{"time":568946,"text":"of completely quadriplegic patients,"},{"time":570790,"text":"and they can control\na cursor or a wheelchair"},{"time":573474,"text":"or, potentially, a robotic arm."},{"time":575031,"text":"These devices are getting smaller"},{"time":576651,"text":"and going into more and more\nof these patients."},{"time":578902,"text":"Still in clinical trials,"},{"time":580138,"text":"but imagine when we can connect\nthese, for example,"},{"time":582563,"text":"to the amazing bionic limb,"},{"time":584203,"text":"such as the DEKA Arm,\nbuilt by Dean Kamen and colleagues,"},{"time":587049,"text":"which has 17 degrees\nof motion and freedom,"},{"time":589093,"text":"and can allow the person who's lost a limb"},{"time":591145,"text":"to have much higher dexterity or control\nthan they've had in the past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594504,"text":"So we're really entering the era\nof wearable robotics, actually."},{"time":597572,"text":"If you haven't lost a limb\nbut had a stroke,"},{"time":599810,"text":"you can wear these augmented limbs."},{"time":601521,"text":"Or if you're a paraplegic -- I've visited\nthe folks at Berkeley Bionics --"},{"time":605041,"text":"they've developed eLEGS."},{"time":606234,"text":"I took this video last week."},{"time":607624,"text":"Here's a paraplegic patient, walking\nby strapping on these exoskeletons."},{"time":611433,"text":"He's otherwise completely\nwheelchair-bound."},{"time":613468,"text":"This is the early era\nof wearable robotics."},{"time":615508,"text":"And by leveraging\nthese sorts of technologies,"},{"time":617811,"text":"we're going to change\nthe definition of disability"},{"time":620172,"text":"to, in some cases, be superability,\nor super-enabling."},{"time":622726,"text":"This is Aimee Mullins, who lost\nher lower limbs as a young child,"},{"time":625940,"text":"and Hugh Herr, who's a professor at MIT,"},{"time":628277,"text":"who lost his limbs in a climbing accident."},{"time":630302,"text":"And now both of them can climb better,\nmove faster, swim differently"},{"time":633721,"text":"with their prosthetics\nthan us normal-abled persons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":637232,"text":"How about other exponentials?"},{"time":638696,"text":"Clearly the obesity trend is exponentially\ngoing in the wrong direction,"},{"time":642130,"text":"including with huge costs."},{"time":643589,"text":"But the trend in medicine\nis to get exponentially smaller."},{"time":646736,"text":"A few examples: we're now in the era\nof \"Fantastic Voyage,\" the iPill."},{"time":650335,"text":"You can swallow this\ncompletely integrated device."},{"time":652760,"text":"It can take pictures of your GI system,"},{"time":654650,"text":"help diagnose and treat\nas it moves through your GI tract."},{"time":657430,"text":"We get into even smaller micro-robots"},{"time":659273,"text":"that will eventually, autonomously,\nmove through your system,"},{"time":662194,"text":"and be able to do things surgeons can't do"},{"time":664275,"text":"in a much less invasive manner."},{"time":665835,"text":"Sometimes these might\nself-assemble in your GI system,"},{"time":668448,"text":"and be augmented in that reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670196,"text":"On the cardiac side,\npacemakers are getting smaller"},{"time":672712,"text":"and much easier to place,"},{"time":674073,"text":"so no need to train an interventional\ncardiologist to place them."},{"time":677180,"text":"And they'll be wirelessly telemetered\nto your mobile devices,"},{"time":680140,"text":"so you can go places\nand be monitored remotely."},{"time":682650,"text":"These are shrinking even further."},{"time":684272,"text":"This one is in prototyping\nby Medtronic; it's smaller than a penny."},{"time":687552,"text":"Artificial retinas, the ability to put\narrays on the back of the eyeball"},{"time":691001,"text":"and allow the blind to see --"},{"time":692449,"text":"also in early trials,\nbut moving into the future."},{"time":694784,"text":"These are going to be game-changing."},{"time":696539,"text":"Or for those of us who are sighted,"},{"time":698251,"text":"how about having\nthe assisted-living contact lens?"},{"time":700637,"text":"Bluetooth, Wi-Fi available --\nbeams back images to your eye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703483,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":704530,"text":"Now, if you have trouble\nmaintaining your diet,"},{"time":706757,"text":"it might help to have some extra imagery"},{"time":708737,"text":"to remind you how many calories\nare going to be coming at you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712395,"text":"How about enabling the pathologist\nto use their cell phone"},{"time":715170,"text":"to see at a microscopic level"},{"time":716740,"text":"and to lumber that data back to the cloud\nand make better diagnostics?"},{"time":720078,"text":"In fact, the whole era\nof laboratory medicine"},{"time":722388,"text":"is completely changing."},{"time":723564,"text":"We can now leverage microfluidics,"},{"time":725541,"text":"like this chip made\nby Steve Quake at Stanford."},{"time":727782,"text":"Microfluidics can replace\nan entire lab of technicians;"},{"time":730442,"text":"put it on a chip, enable thousands\nof tests at the point of care,"},{"time":733605,"text":"anywhere in the world."},{"time":734781,"text":"This will really leverage technology\nto the rural and the underserved"},{"time":738209,"text":"and enable what used to be thousand-dollar\ntests to be done for pennies,"},{"time":741748,"text":"and at the point of care."},{"time":743124,"text":"If we go down the small\npathway a little bit further,"},{"time":745649,"text":"we're entering the era of nanomedicine,"},{"time":747572,"text":"the ability to make devices super-small,"},{"time":749518,"text":"to the point where we can\ndesign red blood cells"},{"time":751862,"text":"or microrobots that monitor\nour blood system or immune system,"},{"time":754961,"text":"or even those that might clear out\nthe clots from our arteries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758073,"text":"Now how about exponentially cheaper?"},{"time":759837,"text":"Not something we usually think\nabout in the era of medicine,"},{"time":762694,"text":"but hard disks used to be 3,400 dollars\nfor 10 megabytes -- exponentially cheaper."},{"time":766622,"text":"In genomics now, the genome\ncost about a billion dollars"},{"time":769308,"text":"about 10 years ago,\nwhen the first one came out."},{"time":771591,"text":"We're now approaching essentially\na $1,000 genome, probably next year."},{"time":774979,"text":"And in two years, a $100 genome."},{"time":776536,"text":"What will we do with $100 genomes?"},{"time":778284,"text":"Soon we'll have millions\nof these tests available."},{"time":780662,"text":"Then it gets interesting, when we start\nto crowd-source that information,"},{"time":784177,"text":"and enter the era\nof true personalized medicine:"},{"time":786447,"text":"the right drug for the right person\nat the right time,"},{"time":789003,"text":"instead of what we're doing now,\nwhich is the same drug for everybody,"},{"time":792320,"text":"blockbuster drug medications,\nwhich don't work for the individual."},{"time":795450,"text":"Many different companies are working\non leveraging these approaches."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798693,"text":"I'll show you a simple example,\nfrom 23andMe again."},{"time":801122,"text":"My data indicates\nI've got about average risk"},{"time":803256,"text":"for developing macular degeneration,\na kind of blindness."},{"time":805971,"text":"But if I take that same data,\nupload it to deCODEme,"},{"time":808621,"text":"I can look at my risk for type 2 diabetes;\nI'm at almost twice the risk."},{"time":812900,"text":"I might want to watch how much dessert\nI have at lunch, for example."},{"time":816141,"text":"It might change my behavior."},{"time":817516,"text":"Leveraging my knowledge\nof my pharmacogenomics:"},{"time":819782,"text":"how my genes modulate,\nwhat my drugs do and what doses I need"},{"time":823141,"text":"will become increasingly important,"},{"time":824856,"text":"and once in the hands\nof individuals and patients,"},{"time":827231,"text":"will make better drug dosing\nand selection available."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829777,"text":"So again, it's not just genes,\nit's multiple details --"},{"time":832643,"text":"our habits, our environmental exposures."},{"time":834786,"text":"When was the last time your doctor\nasked where you've lived?"},{"time":837621,"text":"Geomedicine: where you live,\nwhat you've been exposed to,"},{"time":840356,"text":"can dramatically affect your health."},{"time":842097,"text":"We can capture that information."},{"time":843652,"text":"Genomics, proteomics, the environment --"},{"time":845585,"text":"all this data streaming at us\nindividually and as physicians:"},{"time":848474,"text":"How do we manage it?"},{"time":849650,"text":"We're now entering the era\nof systems medicine, systems biology,"},{"time":852736,"text":"where we can start to integrate\nall this information."},{"time":855261,"text":"And by looking at the patterns,\nfor example, in our blood,"},{"time":858093,"text":"of 10,000 biomarkers in a single test,"},{"time":859930,"text":"we can look at patterns and detect disease\nat a much earlier stage."},{"time":863489,"text":"This is called by Lee Hood,\nthe father of the field, P4 Medicine."},{"time":866947,"text":"We'll be predictive and know\nwhat you're likely to have."},{"time":869597,"text":"We can be preventative;\nthat prevention can be personalized."},{"time":872444,"text":"More importantly,\nit'll be increasingly participatory."},{"time":874997,"text":"Through websites like PatientsLikeMe"},{"time":876860,"text":"or managing your data on Microsoft\nHealthVault or Google Health,"},{"time":879995,"text":"leveraging this together\nin participatory ways"},{"time":882166,"text":"will be increasingly important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883674,"text":"I'll finish up with exponentially better."},{"time":885654,"text":"We'd like to get therapies\nbetter and more effective."},{"time":888195,"text":"Today we treat high blood pressure\nmostly with pills."},{"time":890700,"text":"What if we take a new device,"},{"time":892111,"text":"knock out the nerve vessels\nthat help mediate blood pressure,"},{"time":895021,"text":"and in a single therapy,\nbasically cure hypertension?"},{"time":897650,"text":"This is a new device\ndoing essentially that."},{"time":899735,"text":"It should be on the market\nin a year or two."},{"time":901821,"text":"How about more targeted\ntherapies for cancer?"},{"time":903949,"text":"I'm an oncologist and know that most\nof what we give is essentially poison."},{"time":907522,"text":"We learned at Stanford and other places\nthat we can discover cancer stem cells,"},{"time":911335,"text":"the ones that seem to be really\nresponsible for disease relapse."},{"time":914587,"text":"So if you think of cancer as a weed,"},{"time":916530,"text":"we often can whack the weed away\nand it seems to shrink,"},{"time":919447,"text":"but it often comes back."},{"time":920639,"text":"So we're attacking the wrong target."},{"time":922400,"text":"The cancer stem cells remain,"},{"time":923886,"text":"and the tumor can return\nmonths or years later."},{"time":926166,"text":"We're now learning to identify\nthe cancer stem cells"},{"time":928671,"text":"and identify those as targets\nand go for the long-term cure."},{"time":931811,"text":"We're entering the era\nof personalized oncology,"},{"time":934128,"text":"the ability to leverage\nall of this data together,"},{"time":936515,"text":"analyze the tumor"},{"time":937690,"text":"and come up with a real, specific cocktail\nfor the individual patient."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941028,"text":"I'll close with regenerative medicine."},{"time":942885,"text":"I've studied a lot about stem cells."},{"time":944651,"text":"Embryonic stem cells\nare particularly powerful."},{"time":946877,"text":"We have adult stem cells\nthroughout our body;"},{"time":949012,"text":"we use those in bone marrow\ntransplantation."},{"time":951161,"text":"Geron, last year, started the first trial\nusing human embryonic stem cells"},{"time":954987,"text":"to treat spinal cord injuries."},{"time":956576,"text":"Still a phase I trial, but evolving."},{"time":958650,"text":"We've been using adult stem cells\nin clinical trials for about 15 years"},{"time":962447,"text":"to approach a whole range of topics,\nparticularly cardiovascular disease."},{"time":966050,"text":"If we take our own bone marrow cells\nand treat a patient with a heart attack,"},{"time":969790,"text":"we can see much improved\nheart function and better survival"},{"time":972726,"text":"using our own bone marrow derived cells\nafter a heart attack."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975703,"text":"I invented a device\ncalled the MarrowMiner,"},{"time":977763,"text":"a much less invasive way\nfor harvesting bone marrow."},{"time":980224,"text":"It's now been FDA approved;\nhopefully on the market in the next year."},{"time":983507,"text":"Hopefully you can appreciate the device"},{"time":985408,"text":"going through the patient's body removing\nbone marrow, not with 200 punctures,"},{"time":989202,"text":"but with a single puncture,\nunder local anesthesia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":991619,"text":"Where is stem-cell therapy going?"},{"time":993227,"text":"If you think about it,"},{"time":994402,"text":"every cell in your body has the same DNA\nyou had when you were an embryo."},{"time":997901,"text":"We can now reprogram your skin cells"},{"time":999869,"text":"to actually act like a pluripotent\nembryonic stem cell"},{"time":1002806,"text":"and utilize those, potentially, to treat\nmultiple organs in the same patient,"},{"time":1006478,"text":"making personalized stem cell lines."},{"time":1008225,"text":"I think there'll be a new era\nof your own stem cell banking"},{"time":1011034,"text":"to have in the freezer your own cardiac\ncells, myocytes and neural cells"},{"time":1014526,"text":"to use them in the future,\nshould you need them."},{"time":1016903,"text":"We're integrating this now\nwith a whole era of cellular engineering,"},{"time":1020149,"text":"and integrating exponential technologies\nfor essentially 3D organ printing,"},{"time":1023741,"text":"replacing the ink with cells,"},{"time":1025449,"text":"and essentially building\nand reconstructing a 3D organ."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1028270,"text":"That's where things are heading."},{"time":1029820,"text":"Still very early days,"},{"time":1031005,"text":"but I think, as integration\nof exponential technologies,"},{"time":1033776,"text":"this is the example."},{"time":1034964,"text":"So in closing, as you think\nabout technology trends"},{"time":1037475,"text":"and how to impact health and medicine,"},{"time":1039339,"text":"we're entering an era of miniaturization,"},{"time":1041340,"text":"decentralization and personalization."},{"time":1043586,"text":"And by pulling these things together,"},{"time":1045418,"text":"if we start to think about\nhow to understand and leverage them,"},{"time":1048427,"text":"we're going to empower the patient,\nenable the doctor, enhance wellness"},{"time":1051802,"text":"and begin to cure the well\nbefore they get sick."},{"time":1054273,"text":"Because I know as a doctor, if someone\ncomes to me with stage I disease,"},{"time":1057835,"text":"I'm thrilled; we can often cure them."},{"time":1059650,"text":"But often it's too late,"},{"time":1060844,"text":"and it's stage III or IV\ncancer, for example."},{"time":1062997,"text":"So by leveraging\nthese technologies together,"},{"time":1065136,"text":"I think we'll enter a new era\nthat I like to call stage 0 medicine."},{"time":1068397,"text":"And as a cancer doctor,\nI'm looking forward to being out of a job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1071690,"text":"Thanks very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1072936,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1074938,"text":"Host: Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1076659,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1078483,"text":"Take a bow, take a bow."}]}]}